Kubernetes Pod Health Check (checkpod.sh)

This script checks if a specific Kubernetes pod is running. It uses parameter expansion to set a default pod name and command substitution to capture the pod's status.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#!/bin/bash
# Uses the provided pod_name or defaults to "nginx"
pod_name=${pod_name:-nginx}

# Captures the status of the pod using kubectl and JSON path
status=$(kubectl get pod $pod_name -o jsonpath='{.status.phase}')

if [ "$status" == "Running" ]; then
    echo "$pod_name is healthy"
    exit 0 # Success signal
else
    echo "$pod_name is not healthy"
    exit 1 # Failure signal
fi

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Key Concepts:
Parameter Expansion (${var:-default}): Ensures the script has a value to work with even if no variable is explicitly provided.

Exit Codes: The script uses exit 0 for success and exit 1 for failure, which allows CI/CD pipelines and monitoring tools to react to the script's outcome
